<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<module fritzingVersion="0.5.2b.02.18.4756" moduleId="adafruit_43ef79a2fad9dce1661a27e705b560d7_1_56" referenceFile="Adafruit MPRLS Sensor Breakout.fzp">
 <version>4</version>
 <date>2018-09-26</date>
 <author>adafruit</author>
 <description>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd">
&lt;html>&lt;head>&lt;meta name="qrichtext" content="1" />&lt;style type="text/css">
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style>&lt;/head>&lt;body style=" font-family:'.SF NS Text'; font-size:13pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;">
&lt;p style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">&lt;span style=" font-family:'Helvetica Neue'; color:#454545;">This pressure sensor is special because it comes with a metal port - you can easily attach a tube to it, to measure air pressure inside a close space. In particular we think this would be a great sensor for use with making DIY assistive tech &amp;quot;Sip &amp;amp; Puff&amp;quot; interfaces, or measuring the pressure within a vacuum chamber or other pressurized container. The port is made of stainless steel and is 3.7mm long and 2.5mm diameter.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p style="-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:'Helvetica Neue'; color:#454545;">&lt;br />&lt;/p>
&lt;p style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">&lt;span style=" font-family:'Helvetica Neue'; color:#454545;">Unlike most ported pressure sensors, this one uses I2C, it's really easy to use with any microcontroller. Inside is a silicone-gel covered pressure sensing gauge with a pre-calibrated and compensated 24 bit ADC. You can measure absolute pressure 0 to 25 PSI. We've placed this nice sensor on a breakout board with 3.3V power regulation and level shifting so you can use it with any kind of microcontroller or microcomputer, from an Arduino compatible to Raspberry Pi.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;/body>&lt;/html></description>
 <title>Adafruit MPRLS Sensor Breakout</title>
 <tags/>
